{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.14",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
    "chapterNumber": 14,
    "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 14",
    "summary": "Source text for 1 Chronicles 14 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.14.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 14:1",
      "text": "And Hiram king of Tyre sent messengers to David, and cedar trees, also masons and carpenters to build a house for him.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.14.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 14:2",
      "text": "And David perceived that the Lord had established him king over Israel, and that his kingdom was highly exalted for the sake of his people Israel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.14.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 14:3",
      "text": "And David took more wives in Jerusalem, and David begot more sons and daughters.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.14.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 14:4",
      "text": "These are the names of the children whom he had in Jerusalem: Shammua, Shobab, Nathan, Solomon,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.14.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 14:5",
      "text": "Ibhar, Elishu-a, Elpelet,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.14.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 14:6",
      "text": "Nogah, Nepheg, Japhia,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.14.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 14:7",
      "text": "Elishama, Beeliada, and Eliphelet.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.14.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 14:8",
      "text": "When the Philistines heard that David had been anointed king over all Israel, all the Philistines went up in search of David; and David heard of it and went out against them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.14.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 14:9",
      "text": "Now the Philistines had come and made a raid in the valley of Rephaim.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.14.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 14:10",
      "text": "And David inquired of God, “Shall I go up against the Philistines? Wilt thou give them into my hand?” And the Lord said to him, “Go up, and I will give them into your hand.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.14.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 14:11",
      "text": "And he went up to Baal-perazim, and David defeated them there; and David said, “God has broken through my enemies by my hand, like a bursting flood.” Therefore the name of that place is called Baal-perazim.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.14.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 14:12",
      "text": "And they left their gods there, and David gave command, and they were burned.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.14.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 14:13",
      "text": "And the Philistines yet again made a raid in the valley.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.14.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 14:14",
      "text": "And when David again inquired of God, God said to him, “You shall not go up after them; go around and come upon them opposite the balsam trees.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.14.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 14:15",
      "text": "And when you hear the sound of marching in the tops of the balsam trees, then go out to battle; for God has gone out before you to smite the army of the Philistines.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.14.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 14:16",
      "text": "And David did as God commanded him, and they smote the Philistine army from Gibeon to Gezer.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:first-chronicles.14.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "first-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Chronicles 14:17",
      "text": "And the fame of David went out into all lands, and the Lord brought the fear of him upon all nations.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
